[5] USA (Oregon, Portland and Washington, Vancouver)
Date: Mon 7 Jan 2019
Source: KPIC [abridged, edited]
https://kpic.com/news/local/we-worry-about-outbreaks-from-measles-kind-of-like-a-wildfire-it-just-spreads


Two cases of measles have been confirmed in the northwest: one in Vancouver, Washington, and the other in Portland, Oregon. The Oregon Health Authority says a man with the illness spent time in The Dalles and Hood River. If you visited those areas on 29-30 Dec 2018, you may want to watch out for symptoms.

Lane County Public Health's Dr. Patrick Luedtke says vaccination is key to making sure you don't catch the disease. "We worry about outbreaks from measles kind of like a wildfire," said Dr. Luedtke. "It just spreads. If you have one case and people are susceptible, pretty soon you're going to have hundreds, that's just the way it is."

[Byline: Stephanie Rothman and KVAL.com Staff]

