Africa
---
[8] Uganda (Hoima)
Date: Thu 10 Jan 2019
Source: Xinhua [abriged, edited]
http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2019-01/10/c_137734136.htm


A total of 5 children in the western Ugandan district of Hoima have died of measles, the country's health ministry said on Thu [10 Jan 2019]. Emma Ainebyoona, the ministry's public relations officer, told Xinhua by telephone that all the children were under 10 years of age. The cases occurred in the past week.

The officer said the country is facing a measles outbreak and that 56 districts have already been affected. Ainebyoona urged parents to take their children for vaccination against the disease. "We shall soon roll out the mass measles and rubella immunization campaign before the end of this month [January 2019]," Ainebyoona said.

Measles, according to the ministry of health, is one of the killer diseases among children under 5 years of age. The others include diphtheria, polio and tuberculosis.

